    "body": "I'm also loving the idea of `extern mod`, because it makes it easier to get rid of cargo and unify it with the single `rust` tool idea. That way, it could potentially lead to a URL rather than a file path. e.g. `extern mod sdl = \"git://github.com/brson/rust-sdl.git/sdl.rs\";` or `extern mod sdl = \"http://libsdl.org/rustpkg.tar.gz/sdl.rs\";`.\n",
